<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">workers</ENAMEX> will surely choose not to participate. Moreover, if <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">workers</ENAMEX> are allowed
a wide range of investment choices, then administrative costs, error rates--and
risk--will soar. And even if investments are limited to a relatively small menu
of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">government</ENAMEX>-supervised options, the timing of their contributions or
