alternatives. It will have to cut other spending, raise other taxes or, more
likely, sell other bonds to the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">public</ENAMEX>--that is, run a big budget deficit.
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Social Security</ENAMEX> itself wouldn't go bankrupt. As long as there are still U.S.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">workers</ENAMEX> paying payroll taxes (and if there aren't, we'll have many far bigger
